description.narrative:
Burkina Faso government has developed a favorable legal framework for the participation of women but that is not sufficiently applied.
So the&nbsp; global objective aimed by the project is to contribute to the promotion and protection of socio-cultural and political rights of women and girls in areas of central and north central. And the specific objectives (4) are:
-&nbsp;From 2016 to 2020, increase of 30% women's participation in political and administrative governance in the municipalities of Ouagadougou, Ziniar&eacute;, Kaya and Kongoussi;
- From 2016 to 2020, ownership and facilitate effective implementation of the law on violence against women and girls in the districts of Ouagadougou, Ziniar&eacute;, Kaya and Kongoussi;
- By 2020, enhance the employability of young girls communes of Ouagadougou, Ziniar&eacute;, Kaya and Kongoussi;
- By 2020, reduce the negative impact of unwanted pregnancies on the academic performance of girls in the beneficiary institutions of the project. 
Project actions will focus on:
- Capacity building of women leadership and mangement in order to increase their participation in public decision-making;
-Monitoring of the implementation of the law on violence against girls and women adopted in 2015;
-Capacity building of students and education stakeholders in gender, sexual health and reproduction to reduce school drop especially girls school drop.
The target groups&nbsp;are women and girls, government, ministry, local authorities.
The main thematic focus is women right. &nbsp;&nbsp;
